## PRD Ambiguity (§5.1.1 record of taking the more specific side)

> When the PRD is ambiguous: take "the more specific side" and keep writing, note it here, and re-verify later.

> **Example (greyed example)**
> - **§3.4 login timeout** — PRD only says "re-login on timeout", doesn't define the number of seconds.
>   - Adopted: log out after 30 min idle (aligns with existing session config).
>   - Pending: <await user confirmation of this value>

- **<§section + topic>** — <description of the PRD ambiguity>
  - Adopted: <the specific interpretation I chose>
  - Pending: <point needing user confirmation>

